Document: Mutex  
Path: godot/classes/class_mutex.rst  
Summary: Three core methods for managing thread synchronization: locking, trying to lock, and unlocking a mutex.  

Methods:  
- void lock(): Locks this Mutex, blocks until it is unlocked by the current owner. Note: Returns without blocking if the thread already has ownership of the mutex.  
- bool try_lock(): Tries locking this Mutex without blocking. Returns true on success, false otherwise. Note: Returns true if the thread already has ownership of the mutex.  
- void unlock(): Unlocks this Mutex, allowing other threads to acquire it. Note: If a thread calls lock() or try_lock() multiple times while owning the mutex, it must call unlock() the same number of times to fully release it. Warning: Calling unlock() more times than lock() on a given thread can cause crashes or deadlocks.